issue.body:
Hi,

I'm facing an issue with the dynamic compiler for less.
When I'm compiling staticallyl with Rhino my less file, it's "translated" properly and evertyhing is fine and working as expected.

However, when I'm trying to dynamically compile the same file with less.js, I have a problem with the following statement : 
background-image: url(@bgImg);

If I'm using the variable value instead of @bgImg, it's working as expected. Seems that the variable resolution is not done for "url".

Here is the original snippet of my code (problem is on the h-picture class):
@import "variables.less";

// L'URL de l'image de fond
@bgImg:"../../img/header-image-verte.jpg";

// Tailles de la marianne
@marianneWidth: 114px;
@marianneHeight: 146px;

/**
- L'image de la marianne.
  */
  .h-marianne { 
  background-position:left top;
  width: @marianneWidth;
  vertical-align: top;
  text-decoration: none; 
  border-bottom: 0px;  
  }
  .h-marianne a { 
  text-decoration: none;
  }

/**
- L'image de fond dans l'en-tête.
  */
  .h-picture{
  background-color: #FFFFFF1;
  background-image: -moz-linear-gradient(left center , rgba(255, 255, 255, 1), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0) 100%), url(@bgImg);
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-position:right top;
  padding-left: 0px;
  }

